  "prompt": "How do I recover my Gmail password with a recovery mobile number and a Gmail address?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Gmail password, you can recover it using your recovery mobile number and Gmail address. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Recover Your Gmail Password:**\n\n1. **Go to the Gmail Password Recovery Page:**\n   - Open your browser and go to the [Gmail Password Recovery Page](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery).\n\n2. **Enter Your Gmail Address:**\n   - Enter the Gmail address for which you want to recover the password and click **Next**.\n\n3. **Select \"Forgot Password?\":**\n   - On the next screen, click **Forgot password?**.\n\n4. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will ask how you want to verify your identity. Choose the option to receive a verification code on your **recovery mobile number**.\n\n5. **Enter the Verification Code:**\n   - You\u2019ll receive a text message with a verification code on your recovery mobile number. Enter the code on the recovery page and click **Next**.\n\n6. **Create a New Password:**\n   - Once your identity is verified, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password. Enter a strong, secure password and confirm it.\n\n7. **Sign In with Your New Password:**\n   - After resetting your password, use the new password to sign in to your Gmail account.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips:**\n- Ensure your recovery mobile number is up-to-date in your Google account settings.\n- If you don\u2019t receive the verification code, check if your number is correct and ensure you have a stable mobile network connection.\n- If you encounter issues, you can use other recovery options, such as a recovery email or answering security questions (if set up).\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019re still unable to recover your password, visit the [Google Account Help Center](https://support.google.com/accounts) for additional support.",
